        {
            "title": "與中國裂痕加深之際 日本首相高市早苗將在奈良款待李在明以拉攏韓國",
            "description": "<div class=\"atoms\"><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\"><span class=\"news-dateline\">【彭博】--</span> 日本首相高市早苗將在周二的雙邊峰會上尋求強化與韓國的關係。此舉正值東京努力管控與中國日益加劇的外交和貿易爭端，同時應對北京方面在美國主要盟友之間製造分歧的努力。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">高市早苗將在她家鄉奈良縣會晤韓國總統李在明，這是兩人在不到三個月內舉行的第二次會談。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">李在明的國家安全顧問已暗示，此次會談將涉及中日摩擦問題。不過，鑒於李在明一直試圖避免韓國在兩大強鄰關係日益緊張的情況下選邊站隊，他不太可能公開發表任何針對北京的言論。</p><div class=\"bg-toast-background -mx-5 -mt-2 mb-3 pb-3 md:-mx-0 lg:mx-auto lg:w-[300px] lg:pb-0\"><div class=\"text-px14 text-gandalf py-1 text-center leading-5\">廣告</div><div class=\"mx-auto text-center min-w-[300px] min-h-[250px]\" id=\"sda-inbody-9123e4e4-982d-3ade-b071-d23b5ce1adeb-1-iframe\"><div class=\"bg-dirty-seagull text-px12 text-dolphin mx-auto hidden items-center justify-center only:flex w-[300px] h-[250px]\">廣告</div></div></div><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">What Bloomberg Economics Says...</p><div class=\"recommendation-contents\"><div class=\"bg-marshmallow mb-2 h-[30px] w-[80px] rounded-lg\"></div><div class=\"no-scrollbar -mx-5 mb-5 flex overflow-hidden overflow-x-auto md:-mx-2 lg:mb-3.5\"><div class=\"bg-marshmallow mr-2 ml-5 h-[92px] w-[calc(85%-28px)] flex-shrink-0 rounded-lg md:ml-2 md:w-[calc(85%-16px)] lg:h-[120px] lg:w-[calc(50%-16px)]\"></div><div class=\"bg-marshmallow mx-2 h-[92px] w-[85%] flex-shrink-0 rounded-lg lg:h-[120px] lg:w-[calc(50%-16px)]\"></div></div></div><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">“This week’s summit in Nara between South Korean President Lee Jae Myung and Japanese Prime Minister Sanae Takaichi will test Lee’s ability to balance Seoul’s economic and geopolitical trade-offs, coming straight after his visit to China. The challenge is to turn pragmatism — neither pro- nor anti-China — into tangible progress in Korea-Japan ties.”</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">— Hyosung Kwon, economist, and Adam Farrar, analyst</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">Click here to read full report</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">即使未被明確點名，中國議題預計仍將成為會談的重要背景。日本若能展現與韓國的良好默契，將有助於其爭取盟友支持，以應對中國在全球層面內孤立東京的態勢。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">高市早苗和李在明預計將於周二下午對記者發表講話，隨後於次日一同參觀一座歷史悠久的寺廟。高市早苗還將於周四至周六在日本接待義大利總理喬治亞·梅洛尼。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">原文標題Japan to Court South Korea With China Rift Deepening (1)</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">More stories like this are available on <a class=\"link\" data-ylk=\"slk:bloomberg.com;elm:context_link;itc:0;sec:content-canvas\" href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">bloomberg.com</a></p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">©2026 Bloomberg L.P.</p></div>",
            "link": "https://hk.news.yahoo.com/%E8%88%87%E4%B8%AD%E5%9C%8B%E8%A3%82%E7%97%95%E5%8A%A0%E6%B7%B1%E4%B9%8B%E9%9A%9B-%E6%97%A5%E6%9C%AC%E9%A6%96%E7%9B%B8%E9%AB%98%E5%B8%82%E6%97%A9%E8%8B%97%E5%B0%87%E5%9C%A8%E5%A5%88%E8%89%AF%E6%AC%BE%E5%BE%85%E6%9D%8E%E5%9C%A8%E6%98%8E%E4%BB%A5%E6%8B%89%E6%94%8F%E9%9F%93%E5%9C%8B-014159606.html",
